   138â†’### mitt
   140â†’Mitt: Tiny (~200b) functional event emitter / pubsub.
   141â†’
   142â†’Returns **Mitt** 
   143â†’
   144â†’### all
   146â†’A Map of event names to registered handler functions.
   147â†’
   148â†’### on
   150â†’Register an event handler for the given type.
   151â†’
   152â†’#### Parameters
   154â†’-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** Type of event to listen for, or `'*'` for all events
   155â†’-   `handler` **[Function](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function)** Function to call in response to given event
   156â†’
   157â†’### off
   159â†’Remove an event handler for the given type.
   160â†’If `handler` is omitted, all handlers of the given type are removed.
   161â†’
   162â†’#### Parameters
   164â†’-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** Type of event to unregister `handler` from, or `'*'`
   165â†’-   `handler` **[Function](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Statements/function)?** Handler function to remove
   166â†’
   167â†’### emit
   169â†’Invoke all handlers for the given type.
   170â†’If present, `'*'` handlers are invoked after type-matched handlers.
   171â†’
   172â†’Note: Manually firing '\*' handlers is not supported.
   173â†’
   174â†’#### Parameters
   176â†’-   `type` **([string](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/String) \| [symbol](https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/JavaScript/Reference/Global_Objects/Symbol))** The event type to invoke
   177â†’-   `evt` **Any?** Any value (object is recommended and powerful), passed to each handler
   178â†’
   179â†’## Contribute
   181â†’First off, thanks for taking the time to contribute!
   182â†’Now, take a moment to be sure your contributions make sense to everyone else.
   183â†’
   184â†’### Reporting Issues
   186â†’Found a problem? Want a new feature? First of all see if your issue or idea has [already been reported](../../issues).
   187â†’If don't, just open a [new clear and descriptive issue](../../issues/new).
   188â†’
   189â†’### Submitting pull requests
   191â†’Pull requests are the greatest contributions, so be sure they are focused in scope, and do avoid unrelated commits.
   192â†’
   193â†’-   Fork it!
   194â†’-   Clone your fork: `git clone https://github.com/<your-username>/mitt`
   195â†’-   Navigate to the newly cloned directory: `cd mitt`
   196â†’-   Create a new branch for the new feature: `git checkout -b my-new-feature`
   197â†’-   Install the tools necessary for development: `npm install`
   198â†’-   Make your changes.
   199â†’-   Commit your changes: `git commit -am 'Add some feature'`
   200â†’-   Push to the branch: `git push origin my-new-feature`
   201â†’-   Submit a pull request with full remarks documenting your changes.
   202â†’
